import numpy as np
from scipy.signal import firwin2, freqz, windows
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# : 
#     ,  0.5*f (f -  ),   ,  f
#   Nf = 20

#  
Nf = 20 + 1  #    (  + 1)

#        2 : 
# -    
# -    
window_types = ['boxcar', 'boxcar', 'hamming']
num_coefs = [1001, Nf, Nf]
titles = ['  ', '   ""', '    ']

for i in range(len(window_types)):

    #  FIR   
    filter_coefs = firwin2(num_coefs[i], [0.0, 0.5, 1.0], [1.0, 1.0, 0.0], window=window_types[i])
    
    #   
    w, h = freqz(filter_coefs)
    
    #    
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 2))
    plt.subplot(1,3,1)
    plt.plot(w/np.pi, abs(h))
    plt.title(titles[i])
    plt.xlabel('  [f/f]')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.grid(True)
    
    plt.subplot(1,3,2)
    plt.plot(w/np.pi, 20 * np.log10(abs(h)))
    plt.title(titles[i])
    plt.xlabel('  [f/f]')
    plt.ylabel(' ()')
    plt.grid(True)
    
    #    
    plt.subplot(1,3,3)
    plt.stem(filter_coefs)
    plt.title('  -  ')
    plt.xlabel(' ')
    plt.ylabel(' ')
    plt.grid(True)
